Summary:
This netlist is the transient version of the RC low-pass step response. It applies a fixed voltage source to the RC network and watches the capacitor voltage rise over time.
Because the capacitor starts discharged under `startup`, the waveform clearly shows the classic exponential charging curve.

Line-by-line:
`C1 OUT 0 100µ` is the capacitor node being observed.
`R1 OUT N001 2k` is the charging resistor.
`V1 N001 0 5` is the step source.
`.tran 0 1s 0 1ms startup` runs the time-domain simulation.
The comments explain the expected time constant and cutoff frequency.

Netlist meaning:
This is a direct SPICE deck for observing how a low-pass RC filter responds to a step input.
The output is the capacitor voltage at node `OUT`.
